To only use keyboard shortcuts for working with styles and moving text, and not just text formatting, you can use the `css-select` package to select the elements you want, and then use the keyboard shortcuts for modifying styles or moving text within those selected elements.

For example, to select all text elements in the document using `css-select`, you can use:
```css
!js css-select #text {
  background-color: pink;
}
```
To use this code, you'll need to wrap it in a script element in your HTML, like this:
```php
<script>
  // Your existing script that uses CSS selectors
  console.log(document.querySelector('#text'));
</script>
```
With this code, you'll only use the keyboard shortcuts for modifying styles or moving text on elements that have the class `#text`. This can be more efficient than using the `css-select` package directly on the document level, as it only selects the elements you need, and not the entire document.

